00:52:39,240 --> 00:52:41,071
They want you to come downstairs.

743
00:52:41,160 --> 00:52:44,038
LYDIA: Delia says you can wear
any sheets you want.

744
00:52:45,000 --> 00:52:47,673
It was like being in an amusement park.

745
00:52:48,040 --> 00:52:48,916
Wham!

746
00:52:49,120 --> 00:52:52,669
- I didn't know I could do the calypso.
- Who has more fun than us?

747
00:52:52,760 --> 00:52:55,354
OTHO: We're dealing
with Tracy and Hepburn.

748
00:52:55,680 --> 00:52:59,116
A very sophisticated pair.
They even appear in sheets.

749
00:52:59,200 --> 00:53:00,428
[Cackles]

750
00:53:00,520 --> 00:53:03,592
Charles, why didn't you tell us
about this before?

751
00:53:05,040 --> 00:53:09,556
We're not sure we want our secret out.
Everyone will want them for parties.

752
00:53:09,640 --> 00:53:11,312
People will pay big money for this.

753
00:53:11,400 --> 00:53:15,234
The Enquirer is offering $50,000
for proof of life after death.

754
00:53:17,000 --> 00:53:19,878
This is it, Charles.
You can get Maxie Dean up here now.

755
00:53:19,960 --> 00:53:22,918
- You think so?
- Sarah loves the supernatural.

756
00:53:23,800 --> 00:53:25,916
She'll have him sprint up here
in his helicopter...

757
00:53:26,000 --> 00:53:28,560
...if you can produce ghosts for her.

758
00:53:31,920 --> 00:53:34,753
I should remind you that I'm Delia's agent.

759
00:53:34,840 --> 00:53:37,070
I have lost money on her work for years.

760
00:53:37,160 --> 00:53:39,628
If anything happened here, I shall handle it.

761
00:53:39,720 --> 00:53:41,950
But not until I've seen real proof.

762
00:53:42,040 --> 00:53:45,828
- What about this table?
- What do you call what just happened?

763
00:53:46,120 --> 00:53:48,509
What money?
Don't you believe in my work?

764
00:53:49,400 --> 00:53:50,958
CHARLES: Here's Lydia.

765
00:53:51,440 --> 00:53:54,318
CHARLES: Well?
LYDIA: They don't want to come down.

766
00:54:01,440 --> 00:54:02,668
Why not?

767
00:54:04,360 --> 00:54:08,319
I think they were trying to scare you away,
and you didn't get scared.

768
00:54:08,400 --> 00:54:11,517
They're dead.
It's a little late to be neurotic.

769
00:54:15,360 --> 00:54:16,679
All right.

770
00:54:22,200 --> 00:54:25,078
This was not a hallucination.
This was real.

771
00:54:26,360 --> 00:54:30,876
DELIA: We all experienced a super-powerful
paranormal experience and it was real.

772
00:54:31,560 --> 00:54:34,916
Delia, you are a flake.
You have always been a flake.

773
00:54:35,720 --> 00:54:39,633
If you insist on frightening people,
do it with your sculpture.

774
00:54:40,760 --> 00:54:42,159
CHARLES: Drive carefully!

775
00:54:42,240 --> 00:54:44,276
DELIA: I'm dead.
OTHO: Where do they hide?

776
00:54:44,360 --> 00:54:46,635
- The attic.
- The attic's locked.

777
00:54:47,440 --> 00:54:49,908
They're ghosts.
They can do what they want.

778
00:54:50,000 --> 00:54:53,037
They do whatever they want.
Take us up there right now.

779
00:54:59,200 --> 00:55:02,237
OTHO: Fabulous! Otho Fenlock's
'"Locked Door Ghosts! '"

780
00:55:02,480 --> 00:55:03,993
Probably committed suicide up there.

781
00:55:04,080 --> 00:55:06,230
OTHO: I'm enchanted.
DELIA: In there?

782
00:55:06,320 --> 00:55:09,118
- They must live like animals.
- It's locked. How did they get in?

783
00:55:09,200 --> 00:55:11,760
[Yells] Open this door, Dead People,
or we'll bust it down...

784
00:55:11,840 --> 00:55:14,229
...and drag you out by the ropes
you hanged yourself with!

785
00:55:14,320 --> 00:55:17,039
LYDIA: They didn't commit suicide.
DELIA: It doesn't matter.

786
00:55:17,120 --> 00:55:20,590
I can teach you something here.
Take the upper hand in all situations...

787
00:55:20,680 --> 00:55:23,433
...or people, dead or alive,
will walk all over you.

788
00:55:23,520 --> 00:55:24,748
Open up!

789
00:55:24,840 --> 00:55:26,319
[Door squeaks]

790
00:55:36,600 --> 00:55:38,113
DELIA: Where are they?

791
00:55:38,280 --> 00:55:40,475
LYDIA: These ghosts are nice people.

792
00:55:40,840 --> 00:55:44,355
I think we scared them away,
so let's leave them alone, all right?

793
00:55:44,440 --> 00:55:46,431
It's the whole damn town.

794
00:55:47,640 --> 00:55:50,029
I have never been so embarrassed.

795
00:55:50,920 --> 00:55:52,751
Have they gone for good?

796
00:55:58,800 --> 00:56:00,153
Dad, don't.

797
00:56:00,480 --> 00:56:02,198
LYDIA: Mom, let's just go.

798
00:56:14,400 --> 00:56:15,913
No ghosts here.

799
00:56:18,600 --> 00:56:22,036
Come on! If they are in here,
I don't want to scare them away.

800
00:56:23,840 --> 00:56:26,957
DELIA: We're leaving now.
You can go about your business.

801
00:56:29,040 --> 00:56:32,077
CHARLES: What are we doing?
DELIA: Quick, quick, quick.

802
00:56:32,440 --> 00:56:33,589
[Slam]

803
00:56:34,800 --> 00:56:36,552
[Betelgeuse cackles]

804
00:56:38,720 --> 00:56:41,712
Oh, boy! You guys are really spooksters,
aren't you?

805
00:56:42,680 --> 00:56:46,150
Now, let's turn on the juice
and see what shakes loose.

806
00:56:48,680 --> 00:56:52,309
Otho, get Maxie on the phone.
We've really got something here.

807
00:56:52,400 --> 00:56:56,279
We can turn this place into the world's
leading supernatural research center.

808
00:56:56,360 --> 00:56:59,352
An amusement park. I'll do a presentation.
Lydia will bring the ghosts.

809
00:56:59,440 --> 00:57:02,318
I can't bring the ghosts. They're not here.

810
00:57:02,400 --> 00:57:06,154
DELIA: Otho, can't you do something?
OTHO: If I'm properly motivated.

811
00:57:08,520 --> 00:57:11,159
CHARLES: What type of motivation
do you require?

812
00:57:11,240 --> 00:57:15,028
LYDIA: Why don't you leave them alone?
They didn't do anything to you.

813
00:57:18,320 --> 00:57:19,912
[Eerie rattling]

814
00:57:31,240 --> 00:57:32,514
[Cackles]

815
00:57:41,240 --> 00:57:42,673
[Otho grunts]

816
00:57:46,240 --> 00:57:47,514
[Cackles]

817
00:57:58,320 --> 00:57:59,912
[Charles groans]

818
00:58:00,480 --> 00:58:02,994
We've come for your daughter, Chuck.

819
00:58:03,960 --> 00:58:05,279
Stop! Stop!

820
00:58:06,960 --> 00:58:08,598
[Charles screams]

821
00:58:08,840 --> 00:58:09,989
[Bang]

822
00:58:13,240 --> 00:58:14,719
[Snake hisses]

823
00:58:16,640 --> 00:58:19,234
- Betelgeuse, Betelgeuse, Betelgeuse!
- Oh, no!

824
00:58:21,200 --> 00:58:23,111
Why are you doing this?

825
00:58:24,720 --> 00:58:26,790
Leave me alone, all of you!

826
00:58:30,240 --> 00:58:34,950
Great choice! We spend the next century
hanging out a window or doing tricks.

827
00:58:35,520 --> 00:58:38,114
Maybe they'll leave now.
That snake was a nasty customer.

828
00:58:38,200 --> 00:58:40,236
- He could've hurt somebody.
- But he didn't.

829
00:58:40,320 --> 00:58:42,675
We've got them where we want them.

830
00:58:46,600 --> 00:58:50,388
You losers! How dare you interrupt
a professional while he's working!

831
00:58:50,480 --> 00:58:53,074
I'm not fond of Charles,
but you could've killed him.

832
00:58:53,160 --> 00:58:56,197
I'm just doing my job!
I thought we had a deal.

833
00:58:56,320 --> 00:58:58,311
It's okay. You know why?

834
00:58:58,760 --> 00:59:02,753
I don't want to do business
with you deadbeats anyway, thank you.

835
00:59:03,160 --> 00:59:06,470
The only one I think I can deal with
is Edgar Allan Poe's daughter.

836
00:59:06,560 --> 00:59:09,199
BETELGEUSE: She understands me.
BARBARA: Leave her alone!

837
00:59:09,280 --> 00:59:11,032
[Betelgeuse cackles]

838
00:59:14,240 --> 00:59:15,958
[Betelgeuse groans]

839
00:59:21,160 --> 00:59:23,355
Go ahead, make my millennium.

840
00:59:23,640 --> 00:59:25,392
[Betelgeuse cackles]

841
00:59:30,600 --> 00:59:34,036
I'm feeling a little anxious,
if you know what I mean.

842
00:59:34,480 --> 00:59:36,516
It's been about 600 years.

843
00:59:36,920 --> 00:59:39,878
I wonder where an everyday Joe
like myself...

844
00:59:40,600 --> 00:59:42,591
...can find a little action.

845
00:59:42,680 --> 00:59:44,159
[Girl squeals]

846
00:59:53,680 --> 00:59:55,352
[Rock music plays]

847
00:59:58,920 --> 01:00:00,911
Yeah. Here I come, baby.

848
01:00:05,120 --> 01:00:06,792
Hey, Adam, nice move!

849
01:00:08,400 --> 01:00:10,834
- Why did you build that?
- I didn't.

850
01:00:12,240 --> 01:00:13,719
[Wind gusting]

851
01:00:20,560 --> 01:00:22,790
JUNO: Will you guys shut up
and leave me alone?

852
01:00:22,880 --> 01:00:25,110
I've got all this paperwork to do.

853
01:00:27,320 --> 01:00:29,276
You two, come in. Sit down.

854
01:00:29,360 --> 01:00:31,351
JUNO: Get in here, both of you!

855
01:00:34,840 --> 01:00:38,833
The whorehouse was my idea.
I want Betelgeuse out of the picture.

856
01:00:39,920 --> 01:00:41,990
You two have really screwed up.

857
01:00:42,480 --> 01:00:45,358
I heard you allowed yourselves
to be photographed.

858
01:00:45,440 --> 01:00:48,079
You let Betelgeuse out
and didn't put him back.

859
01:00:48,160 --> 01:00:50,435
And you let Otho take the handbook!

860
01:00:50,520 --> 01:00:51,635
When?

861
01:00:52,880 --> 01:00:54,791
Never trust the living!

862
01:00:55,360 --> 01:00:57,920
We cannot have
a routine haunting like yours...

863
01:00:58,000 --> 01:01:01,436
...provide proof that there is existence
beyond death.

864
01:01:02,240 --> 01:01:04,879
FOOTBALL PLAYER:
Coach, where's the men's room?

865
01:01:05,640 --> 01:01:08,029
I'm not your coach. He survived.

866
01:01:08,120 --> 01:01:10,190
FOOTBALL PLAYER:
Let me get something straight.

867
01:01:10,280 --> 01:01:12,794
- What's our curfew?
- Get out of here!

868
01:01:13,760 --> 01:01:16,228
Go on, get downstairs! Men's room!

869
01:01:16,800 --> 01:01:19,268
JUNO: Are you kidding?
Can't you read signs?

870
01:01:19,360 --> 01:01:21,078
I'll be right back.

871
01:01:32,840 --> 01:01:34,876
Maybe this was a bad idea.

872
01:01:35,240 --> 01:01:37,071
I didn't say anything.

873
01:01:38,960 --> 01:01:41,758
Who are we kidding?
You've never had a bad idea.

874
01:01:41,840 --> 01:01:42,955
Yeah?

875
01:01:45,600 --> 01:01:47,556
This could all work out.

876
01:01:49,160 --> 01:01:50,149
Home.

877
01:01:53,520 --> 01:01:56,034
I'm not sure this is the right environment
for Lydia.

878
01:01:56,120 --> 01:01:58,111
- Snakes. Ghosts.
- Shrimp.

879
01:01:59,840 --> 01:02:01,478
OTHO: You family types.

880
01:02:01,560 --> 01:02:05,189
You've got other things to worry about.
Maxie Dean is coming tonight.

881
01:02:05,280 --> 01:02:08,636
You have to sell these ghosts.
I can only do so much.

882
01:02:09,040 --> 01:02:12,157
What are you going to do?
Viciously rearrange their environment?

883
01:02:12,240 --> 01:02:16,233
I know as much about the supernatural
as I do about interior design.

884
01:02:21,160 --> 01:02:23,549
[Ltalian opera plays, background]

885
01:02:23,800 --> 01:02:25,028
LYDIA: "I am...

886
01:02:25,440 --> 01:02:26,509
'"...alone.

887
01:02:36,640 --> 01:02:37,834
'"I am...

888
01:02:38,720 --> 01:02:40,199
'"...utterly...

889
01:02:40,440 --> 01:02:41,509
'"...alone.

890
01:02:43,000 --> 01:02:44,513
'"By the time...

891
01:02:46,240 --> 01:02:47,719
'"...you read this...

892
01:02:48,400 --> 01:02:49,833
'"...I will...

893
01:02:50,240 --> 01:02:51,434
'"...be gone...

894
01:02:52,960 --> 01:02:54,632
'"...having jumped...

895
01:02:56,840 --> 01:02:58,592
'"Having plummeted...

896
01:03:00,440 --> 01:03:01,509
'"...off...

897
01:03:02,280 --> 01:03:04,350
'"...the Winter River Bridge.'"

898
01:03:07,320 --> 01:03:09,390
I don't care what it takes.

899
01:03:09,480 --> 01:03:11,994
You get the Deetzes out of there now!

900
01:03:13,280 --> 01:03:14,759
Wait a minute.

901
01:03:16,760 --> 01:03:18,432
What are you going to do?

902
01:03:19,000 --> 01:03:20,479
To scare them.

903
01:03:20,920 --> 01:03:23,878
I want to make sure
it's not some silly parlor trick.

904
01:03:24,480 --> 01:03:25,959
I'll go first.

905
01:03:47,280 --> 01:03:48,952
Not bad. Not bad.

906
01:03:50,320 --> 01:03:51,309
Now you.

907
01:03:51,840 --> 01:03:53,114
JUNO: Go ahead!

908
01:04:07,440 --> 01:04:08,953
You look great.

909
01:04:09,600 --> 01:04:13,593
Go clean house and don't forget
the photographs and the handbook.

910
01:04:22,080 --> 01:04:24,150
FOOTBALL PLAYER: Coach?
JUNO: What?

911
01:04:25,000 --> 01:04:27,230
I don't think we survived that crash.

912
01:04:27,320 --> 01:04:28,912
How did you guess?

913
01:04:32,400 --> 01:04:34,231
Mr. And Mrs. Maitland?

914
01:04:38,800 --> 01:04:39,949
Hello?

915
01:04:41,080 --> 01:04:43,355
LYDIA: Where are you?
BETELGEUSE: Dead.

916
01:04:44,280 --> 01:04:46,271
BETELGEUSE: Dead, dead, deadski.

917
01:04:47,640 --> 01:04:49,437
Of course they're dead. They're ghosts.

918
01:04:49,520 --> 01:04:53,354
No, I mean they're gone. Split.
Out of here. Afterlife kids.

919
01:04:53,880 --> 01:04:56,678
BETELGEUSE: Deceased.
LYDIA: Are you a ghost, too?

920
01:04:58,160 --> 01:05:00,594
I'm the ghost with the most, babe.

921
01:05:02,840 --> 01:05:05,513
You look like somebody I can relate to.

922
01:05:07,200 --> 01:05:09,953
Maybe you could help me get out of here.

923
01:05:10,400 --> 01:05:12,914
I gotta tell you, this death thing...

924
01:05:15,960 --> 01:05:17,313
It's creepy.

925
01:05:17,400 --> 01:05:19,311
BETELGEUSE: Here's my problem.

926
01:05:19,480 --> 01:05:22,597
I've got friends on the outside
I said I'd meet.

927
01:05:23,000 --> 01:05:25,150
I have to be there in person.

928
01:05:25,240 --> 01:05:27,470
So could you help me get out of here?

929
01:05:28,560 --> 01:05:30,198
I want to get in.

930
01:05:31,160 --> 01:05:32,149
Why?

931
01:05:33,840 --> 01:05:37,469
You've probably got your reasons,
but I can't do anything from here.

932
01:05:37,560 --> 01:05:41,155
If you could get me out, over there,
maybe we could talk.

933
01:05:42,280 --> 01:05:45,636
But to do that you've got
to say my name three times.

934
01:05:45,720 --> 01:05:47,358
What's your name?

935
01:05:47,880 --> 01:05:49,757
BETELGEUSE: I can't tell you.

936
01:05:50,040 --> 01:05:51,029
Why not?

937
01:05:51,560 --> 01:05:55,439
If I tell you, you'll tell your friends,
they'll call me all the time.

938
01:05:55,520 --> 01:05:59,433
I've got to go to shopping centers for
openings, sign autographs, that shit.

939
01:05:59,520 --> 01:06:02,478
It makes my life hell, okay? A living hell.

940
01:06:02,960 --> 01:06:06,714
But maybe if you have a pen...
I know! Do you play charades?

941
01:06:07,080 --> 01:06:08,957
LYDIA: Yeah.
BETELGEUSE: Good.

942
01:06:09,240 --> 01:06:10,958
Here we go. Ready?

943
01:06:11,160 --> 01:06:12,479
Two words.

944
01:06:13,120 --> 01:06:14,269
Right!

945
01:06:15,760 --> 01:06:17,796
First word, two syllables.

946
01:06:18,480 --> 01:06:19,595
Look.

947
01:06:20,600 --> 01:06:21,999
Turn around.

948
01:06:23,640 --> 01:06:25,471
I don't know what your signal means.

949
01:06:25,560 --> 01:06:27,152
Look behind you!

950
01:06:27,840 --> 01:06:29,478
Hi. How are you?

951
01:06:29,920 --> 01:06:31,114
Beetle.

952
01:06:31,360 --> 01:06:33,032
Got it. Now, two.

953
01:06:36,120 --> 01:06:38,588
Breakfast? Orange? Orange beetle?

954
01:06:38,720 --> 01:06:40,153
LYDIA: Beetle fruit?

955
01:06:40,640 --> 01:06:42,278
Beetle breakfast?

956
01:06:43,280 --> 01:06:44,759
LYDIA: Beetle drink?

957
01:06:47,360 --> 01:06:48,793
Beetle juice?

958
01:06:48,920 --> 01:06:51,388
- That's it!
- Your name's Beetlejuice?

959
01:06:51,480 --> 01:06:54,756
You said it twice.
Just say it once more. Come on.

960
01:06:55,000 --> 01:06:57,434
It was you, wasn't it? The snake.

961
01:06:58,560 --> 01:07:01,393
You kids and your imagination!
Just say it!

962
01:07:02,480 --> 01:07:03,515
No.

963
01:07:05,240 --> 01:07:06,309
I want to talk to Barbara.

964
01:07:06,400 --> 01:07:09,437
You don't need to talk to Barbara!
Just say it!

965
01:07:13,280 --> 01:07:16,670
BARBARA: Adam, I can't go through
with it. I like that little girl.

966
01:07:16,760 --> 01:07:20,036
But it's too late.
We have to go through with this.

967
01:07:20,320 --> 01:07:22,550
No, we don't. Can't we rebel?

968
01:07:24,640 --> 01:07:26,039
[Adam sighs]

969
01:07:27,240 --> 01:07:28,434
Barbara...

970
01:07:29,440 --> 01:07:31,396
I want to be with Lydia.

971
01:07:42,080 --> 01:07:43,911
Come on! Just say it!

972
01:07:46,040 --> 01:07:47,758
BARBARA: No, don't say it!

973
01:07:48,760 --> 01:07:49,954
Say it!

974
01:07:50,560 --> 01:07:53,199
BARBARA: It's okay. It's us.
What's going on?

975
01:07:54,560 --> 01:07:55,788
- Beetle...
- Shh!

976
01:07:56,280 --> 01:07:59,670
He said if I let him out he would
take me to the other side to find you.

977
01:07:59,760 --> 01:08:01,591
No, Lydia, we're dead.

978
01:08:04,040 --> 01:08:05,951
- I want to be dead, too.
- No!

979
01:08:14,240 --> 01:08:17,038
Being dead doesn't make things any easier.

980
01:08:17,120 --> 01:08:20,908
Listen to her on this.
This is something we know a lot about.

981
01:08:21,920 --> 01:08:24,559
And you can visit us anytime you want.

982
01:08:26,120 --> 01:08:29,192
I have a feeling things are going
to be better from now on.

983
01:08:29,280 --> 01:08:30,474
[Adam grunts]

984
01:08:30,680 --> 01:08:32,671
What do you mean, better?

985
01:08:32,880 --> 01:08:36,839
We've decided we're going to invite
you and your family to stay.

986
01:08:37,920 --> 01:08:39,319
